   <string name="menu_instructions_title">Instructions</string>
   <string name="setupInstructionsString">Pair your Android device to PIXEL which will show up as \'PIXEL\' in Bluetooth using code 0000 for PIXEL V2 and 4545 for PIXEL V1.\n\nTap an image to display it on PIXEL.\n\nLong tap to write an image to PIXEL if you have PIXEL V2 or above unit\n\nSwipe from left to right to start a Slide Show and swipe from right to left to stop the Slide Show.\n\nFollow the instructions below to add your own images to this app:\n\nConnect your Android device to your computer with a USB cable.\n\nFrom your computer, open your Android device and copy your images to the pixel/pngs folder of your SD card or internal storage if your device does not have a removeable SD card.\n\nYou can also delete the sample images leaving only your images.\n\nYou\&apos;ll get the best results by pre-scaling your images to 32x32 resolution.\n\nAny image not in 32x32 resolution will be scaled automatically to 32x32.</string>
